Following hours of uncertainty regarding the authenticity of reports that President Muhammadu Buhari had appointed Prof. Ibrahim Gambari as his new Chief of Staff, the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha, has finally confirmed Gambari as CoS. The SGF made the announcement at the virtual Federal Executive Council meeting on Wednesday. The Point had reported that Gambari arrived the Presidential Villa at about 11am, and was received by senior officials in the Presidency. Prof. Gambari, a Nigerian scholar, diplomat and an indigene of Kwara State, was appointed to replace the late Abba Kyari. Kyari died from COVID-19 related complications on April 17, 2020. Gambari was the Minister of External Affairs between 1984 and 1985 and had served meritoriously in the United Nations as Under Secretary General and Special Adviser to the Secretary General on Africa between 1999 and 2005. Aged 78, he is the pioneer Chancellor of the Kwara State University. 